It's something I have had to do to allow me to accept certain things that have happened in my life so that I could move on from those things and as much of a positive way as I can so that I'm not stuck trying to figure out why something is happened or how something could have happened or who's responsible. That's what I had to do to be able to live my life the rest of it anyway the best I can and continue to strive to be better than I was the day before without having these experiences sitting on my shoulders as deadly because I couldn't get past the questioning of why how and the blaming. It's what I had to do for me to be able to forgive and live without bitterness and anger and resentment.

["Saw a video, gif, or other media of a robot being physically abused or attacked by humans","Had a conversation with a robot/AI","Had a conversation with a family member or friend about robots/AIs"]

feedback: A lot of the analysis of these issues becomes definitional.  You scratch upon the big issue, which is are humans different than other beings; and even if they are different from nature (does a tree have a spirit?).  Why would one accept a tree having a spirit and not a rock?  The other issue is robots by definition will be property.  So they would likely have certain rights derived from ownership by someone.  This puts the analysis in an entirely different light.  Maybe a reason not to abuse a robot.  Bottom line to me - robots are our creation.  They are not even nature's creation.  So I put them below rocks, trees and certainly animals.  That being said there might be a tangible wrong inside a person who gets off on torturing robots..
Lots to think about for the future.
